modules.description: This module provides dynamic array operations with efficient resizing, element manipulation, and stack-like behavior, offering amortized O(1) time complexity for insertions and deletions. It works with generic dynamic arrays (`Vector.t`) that use a user-defined dummy value to manage unused slots, automatically expanding and shrinking their internal storage while maintaining locality. Key use cases include high-performance stack implementations, functional transformations (map/fold), and scenarios requiring compact, mutable sequences with controlled memory overhead.
